description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has opened in the South East Essex Dementia and Older People’s Community Mental Health Services to join the locality teams. The role is in the secondary care mental health team (OPCMHT) and will provide support and care coordination to individuals within the locality. The post holder is supported by a the OPCMHT team lead and the Locality Community Dementia Nurse Specialist and the wider teams in the service to ensure excellent quality of care and support to the practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the post holder you will ensure all care is delivered in accordance with the Trust’s policies and procedures. The post holder’s main roles will be to support the physical health needs of individuals receiving care from the service and to support physical health knowledge in other team members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work effectively as part of a multi-disciplinary team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent observation skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of current Mental Health developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EPUT are looking for motivated staff who shares our Trust values of Open, Compassionate and Empowering. In return, EPUT can offer you a range of benefits and development including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season Ticket Loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts for staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent Training facilities and opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work bank shifts and expand knowledge and experience in other areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary Sacrifice schemes including lease cars and Cycle to Work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Buying and Selling annual leave scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSpencer DinnageJob titleOperational Service ManagerEmail addressspencer.dinnage@nhs.netTelephone number07538 799612&lt;/p&gt;
